'''Takenukawawake''' (武渟川別命, ''Takenukawawake''), also referred to as ''Takenunakawawake'' or ''Takenukawawake no Mikoto,'' is a legendary {{ill|Japanese prince|ja|皇族|12=draft}} from the {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|12=draft}}. 

The ''{{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft}}'' refers to him as "Takenukawawake" or "Takenukawabake," while the ''{{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft}}'' uses the name "Takenunakawawake no Mikoto" (建沼河別命). He is known as a son of {{ill|Ōhiko no Mikoto|ja|大彦命|12=draft}}, a prince of {{ill|Emperor Kōgen|ja|孝元天皇|12=draft}}, and is regarded as the ancestor of the {{ill|Abe clan|ja|阿倍氏|12=draft}}.

Takenukawawake was one of the {{ill|Four Commanders of the Four Roads|ja|四道将軍|1=Shidō Shōgun|12=draft}}, who were dispatched to pacify different regions of Japan. He was sent to the {{ill|Tōkaidō region|ja|東海道|12=draft}}. During the reign of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|12=draft}}, he was recognized as one of the five ''maetsukimi'' (大夫), or "chief retainers."

== Historical Records ==

=== Genealogy ===
